  "prompt": "Will I pass a drug test in 2 weeks as a non regular smoker?",
  "response": "Whether you'll pass a drug test in two weeks as a non-regular smoker depends on several factors, including the type of drug test being administered, your metabolism, body fat percentage, the potency of the cannabis you've used, and how much you've consumed.\n\n**General Detection Times for THC (the active component in cannabis):**\n\n1. **Urine Tests:**\n   - **Single Use (Non-Regular Smoker):** THC metabolites are typically detectable for up to 3 days after use.\n   - **Moderate Use:** Detection can extend to about a week.\n   - **Chronic Use:** For regular users, THC metabolites might be detectable for several weeks.\n\n2. **Blood Tests:**\n   - THC is usually detectable in the blood for up to 1-2 days after use for occasional users.\n\n3. **Saliva Tests:**\n   - Typically, THC can be detected in saliva for up to 24-72 hours after use.\n\n4. **Hair Tests:**\n   - THC can be detected in hair follicles for up to 90 days, but hair tests are less common for employment purposes.\n\n**Given that you are a non-regular smoker:**\n\n- **Urine Tests:** It's likely that THC metabolites will no longer be detectable after two weeks, especially if you\u2019ve only used cannabis a few times.\n- **Blood and Saliva Tests:** These are less likely to detect THC after a couple of weeks since THC clears from the bloodstream and saliva relatively quickly.\n- **Hair Tests:** THC can still be detected in hair for up to 90 days, regardless of usage frequency.\n\n**Additional Factors to Consider:**\n\n- **Metabolism:** Individuals with faster metabolisms may process and eliminate THC more quickly.\n- **Body Fat:** THC metabolites are stored in fat cells. Individuals with higher body fat percentages may retain THC for longer periods.\n- **Hydration and Exercise:** Staying well-hydrated and engaging in regular exercise can potentially aid in speeding up the elimination of THC, though these methods are not guaranteed to ensure a negative test result.\n\n**Final Thoughts:**\n\nFor a non-regular smoker, passing a urine, blood, or saliva test within two weeks is generally achievable. However, results can vary based on the factors mentioned above. If you're concerned about an upcoming drug test, it's essential to allow as much time as possible for your body to naturally eliminate THC metabolites.\n\nRemember, the only guaranteed way to pass a drug test is to abstain from using the substance. If you have specific concerns or need advice related to drug use and testing, consider consulting a healthcare professional.",
